==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stigmatic
<hw>Stig*mat"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
notorious profligate or criminal who has been branded; one who bears the
marks of infamy or punishment.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bullokar.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person who is marked or deformed by nature.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- <sn>3.</sn> <def>A person bearing the wounds on the hands and
feet resembling those of Jesus Christ caused by His crucifixion; -- for
true <ex>stigmantics</ex> the wounds are supposed to have been caused
miraculously, as a sign of great holiness.</def> -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stigmatical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Stigmatic</ent>⟦br⟧
